  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <title>Recursion - Interactive Demonstrations</title>\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial; margin: 18px; color: #111; }\n    h1 { margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 26px; }\n    p { margin: 8px 0; line-height: 1.4; color: #333; }\n    .container { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 18px; max-width: 1000px; }\n    .card { border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; background: #fff; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02); }\n    .row { display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:8px; }\n    label { font-size: 14px; }\n    input[type=\"number\"] { width:80px; padding:6px; font-size:14px; }\n    button { padding:8px 12px; font-size:14px; cursor:pointer; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #cfcfcf; background:#fafafa; }\n    button:disabled { opacity:0.6; cursor:not-allowed; }\n    pre { background:#f7f7f7; padding:10px; border-radius:6px; overflow:auto; max-height:220px; }\n    .stackView { min-height: 40px; border-radius:6px; padding:8px; background:#f4f8ff; border:1px dashed #d0e4ff; }\n    .frame { background:#e9f2ff; border:1px solid #cfe6ff; padding:6px 8px; margin:6px 0; border-radius:6px; }\n    .frame.return { background:#e8ffe8; border:1px solid #bff2bf; }\n    .stackTitle { font-size:13px; margin-bottom:6px; color:#155; }\n    canvas { border:1px solid #ddd; background:#fff; border-radius:6px; }\n    .small { font-size:13px; color:#555; }\n    .footerNote { font-size:13px; color:#666; margin-top:8px; }\n    .controls { display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap; }\n    .badge { background:#eef; color:#114; padding:4px 8px; border-radius:999px; font-weight:600; font-size:12px; }\n    .muted { color:#6b6b6b; font-size:13px; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Recursion — Interactive Demonstrations</h1>\n  <p>\n    Recursion is when a function calls itself to solve a smaller piece of the same problem.\n    Below are interactive examples: a factorial with an animated call stack, a visual recursion tree for Fibonacci,\n    and a recursive drawing (Sierpinski triangle). Try small inputs first (recursion depth grows quickly).\n  </p>\n\n  <div class=\"container\">\n\n    <!-- Factorial with call stack visualization -->\n    <div class=\"card\" id=\"factorialCard\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>Example 1 — Factorial (n!) with animated call stack</strong>\n          <div class=\"small muted\">Watch frames be pushed as the recursion goes deeper, then popped as results return.</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"badge\">Concept: recursion & call stack</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n        <label>n = <input id=\"factN\" type=\"number\" min=\"0\" max=\"12\" value=\"6\" /></label>\n        <button id=\"runFact\">Run Recursion</button>\n        <button id=\"runFactFast\">Run Without Delay</button>\n        <div class=\"muted\">Result: <span id=\"factResult\">—</span></div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n        <div class=\"stackTitle\">Call stack (top is most recent call):</div>\n        <div id=\"stack\" class=\"stackView\"></div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <strong>Recursive implementation (conceptual):</strong>\n        <pre id=\"factCode\">function factorial(n) {\n  if (n <= 1) return 1;\n  return n * factorial(n - 1);\n}</pre>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Fibonacci recursion tree -->\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <strong>Example 2 — Fibonacci recursion tree (naive)</strong>\n      <div class=\"small muted\">This shows the many repeated calls in naive recursion for Fibonacci. Keep n small (≤7).</div>\n\n      <div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <label>n = <input id=\"fibN\" type=\"number\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" value=\"6\" /></label>\n        <button id=\"drawFib\">Draw Tree</button>\n        <label style=\"margin-left:8px;\"><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"showValues\" checked /> Show computed values</label>\n        <div class=\"muted\" style=\"margin-left:auto\">Total calls: <span id=\"fibCalls\">—</span></div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n        <canvas id=\"fibCanvas\" width=\"760\" height=\"300\"></canvas>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <strong>Naive recursive implementation (conceptual):</strong>\n        <pre>function fib(n) {\n  if (n <= 1) return n;\n  return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2);\n}</pre>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Recursive drawing -->\n    <div class=\"card\">\n      <strong>Example 3 — Recursive drawing: Sierpinski triangle</strong>\n      <div class=\"small muted\">A geometric fractal built by recursion: draw a triangle, then 3 smaller triangles inside, and repeat.</div>\n\n      <div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <label>Depth = <input id=\"depth\" type=\"number\" min=\"0\" max=\"7\" value=\"4\" /></label>\n        <button id=\"drawSier\">Draw</button>\n        <div style=\"margin-left:auto\" class=\"muted\">Try depths 0–6 for best performance.</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n        <canvas id=\"sierCanvas\" width=\"760\" height=\"360\"></canvas>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n        <strong>Recursive idea (conceptual):</strong>\n        <pre>function drawTriangle(a, b, c, depth) {\n  if (depth === 0) fillTriangle(a, b, c);\n  else {\n    // compute midpoints and call drawTriangle on 3 corners\n    drawTriangle(a, mid(a,b), mid(a,c), depth-1);\n    drawTriangle(b, mid(b,a), mid(b,c), depth-1);\n    drawTriangle(c, mid(c,a), mid(c,b), depth-1);\n  }\n}</pre>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"footerNote\">\n    Tip: Recursion is powerful for problems that can be broken into similar subproblems. Be careful with base cases and depth to avoid infinite recursion.\n  </div>\n\n  <script>\n    // Utility\n    function $(id){ return document.getElementById(id); }\n    function sleep(ms){ return new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, ms)); }\n\n    // ===== Factorial visualization (async recursive to allow animation) =====\n    (function(){\n      const stackEl = $('stack');\n      const resultEl = $('factResult');\n      const nInput = $('factN');\n      const runBtn = $('runFact');\n      const fastBtn = $('runFactFast');\n\n      let animateDelay = 500;\n\n      function renderStack(frames){\n        // Render from top to bottom (top is most recent call)\n        stackEl.innerHTML = '';\n        if (frames.length === 0){\n          stackEl.textContent = '(empty)';\n          return;\n        }\n        for (let i = frames.length - 1; i >= 0; i--){\n          const f = frames[i];\n          const div = document.createElement('div');\n          div.className = 'frame' + (f.returned ? ' return' : '');\n          div.textContent = f.returned ? `return ${f.n}: ${f.value}` : `call factorial(${f.n})`;\n          stackEl.appendChild(div);\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Async recursive factorial with UI updates\n      async function recFactorial(n, frames){\n        frames.push({ n, returned: false });\n        renderStack(frames);\n        await sleep(animateDelay);\n\n        let value;\n        if (n <= 1) {\n          value = 1;\n        } else {\n          const sub = await recFactorial(n - 1, frames);\n          value = n * sub;\n        }\n\n        // mark returned\n        frames[frames.length - 1].returned = true;\n        frames[frames.length - 1].value = value;\n        renderStack(frames);\n        await sleep(animateDelay);\n        frames.pop();\n        renderStack(frames);\n        await sleep(animateDelay / 2);\n        return value;\n      }\n\n      async function run(quick){\n        const n = Math.max(0, Math.min(12, parseInt(nInput.value) || 0));\n        animateDelay = quick ? 0 : 450;\n        runBtn.disabled = true; fastBtn.disabled = true; nInput.disabled = true;\n        resultEl.textContent = 'running...';\n        try {\n          const frames = [];\n          const v = await recFactorial(n, frames);\n          resultEl.textContent = String(v);\n        } catch (e){\n          resultEl.textContent = 'error';\n          console.error(e);\n        } finally {\n          runBtn.disabled = false; fastBtn.disabled = false; nInput.disabled = false;\n        }\n      }\n\n      runBtn.addEventListener('click', () => run(false));\n      fastBtn.addEventListener('click', () => run(true));\n\n      // initial render\n      renderStack([]);\n      resultEl.textContent = '—';\n    })();\n\n    // ===== Fibonacci recursion tree drawing (naive) =====\n    (function(){\n      const canvas = $('fibCanvas');\n      const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\n      const drawBtn = $('drawFib');\n      const nInput = $('fibN');\n      const callsEl = $('fibCalls');\n      const showValuesCheck = $('showValues');\n\n      function clear(){\n        ctx.clearRect(0,0,canvas.width,canvas.height);\n      }\n\n      // We'll compute positions for a binary recursion tree.\n      // For small n (<=8) we can draw it comfortably.\n\n      function computeTree(n){\n        // returns node object {n, x, y, children: [...]}\n        // We'll place levels by y coordinate, and spread nodes horizontally depending on the number of leaves.\n        // First compute sizes (# of leaves for each subtree) to determine spacing.\n        function leavesCount(k){\n          if (k <= 1) return 1;\n          return leavesCount(k-1) + leavesCount(k-2);\n        }\n        const totalLeaves = leavesCount(n);\n\n        // allocate horizontal positions for leaves\n        let nextX = 40;\n        const gapX = Math.max(20, (canvas.width - 80) / totalLeaves);\n\n        function build(k, depth){\n          if (k <= 1){\n            const node = { n: k, children: [] };\n            node.x = nextX;\n            node.y = 30 + depth * 50;\n            nextX += gapX;\n            return node;\n          } else {\n            const left = build(k-1, depth+1);\n            const right = build(k-2, depth+1);\n            const node = { n: k, children:[left,right] };\n            node.x = (left.x + right.x)/2;\n            node.y = 30 + depth * 50;\n            return node;\n          }\n        }\n        return build(n, 0);\n      }\n\n      // Count function calls in naive recursion\n      function countCalls(n){\n        let cnt = 0;\n        function c(k){\n          cnt++;\n          if(k <= 1) return k;\n          c(k-1); c(k-2);\n        }\n        c(n);\n        return cnt;\n      }\n\n      function drawNode(node, showValues){\n        // draw lines to children first\n        if (node.children.length){\n          for (const ch of node.children){\n            // line\n            ctx.beginPath();\n            ctx.moveTo(node.x, node.y + 12);\n            ctx.lineTo(ch.x, ch.y - 12);\n            ctx.strokeStyle = '#bbb';\n            ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n            ctx.stroke();\n            drawNode(ch, showValues);\n          }\n        }\n        // draw circle for node\n        ctx.beginPath();\n        ctx.fillStyle = '#fff';\n        ctx.strokeStyle = '#2b6ea3';\n        ctx.lineWidth = 1.6;\n        ctx.arc(node.x, node.y, 16, 0, Math.PI*2);\n        ctx.fill();\n        ctx.stroke();\n\n        // label: n\n        ctx.fillStyle = '#113';\n        ctx.font = '12px system-ui, Arial';\n        ctx.textAlign = 'center';\n        ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\n        ctx.fillText(String(node.n), node.x, node.y - 6);\n\n        if (showValues){\n          // compute value recursively (small n only)\n          const val = (function fib(k){\n            if (k <= 1) return k;\n            return fib(k-1) + fib(k-2);\n          })(node.n);\n          ctx.fillStyle = '#2b6ea3';\n          ctx.font = '11px system-ui, Arial';\n          ctx.fillText(String(val), node.x, node.y + 8);\n        }\n      }\n\n      function draw(){\n        const n = Math.max(0, Math.min(10, parseInt(nInput.value) || 0));\n        clear();\n        // small guard for size\n        if (n > 9) {\n          ctx.fillStyle = '#900';\n          ctx.fillText('Choose n ≤ 9 for a readable tree', 20, 20);\n          return;\n        }\n        const calls = countCalls(n);\n        callsEl.textContent = String(calls);\n        const tree = computeTree(n);\n        drawNode(tree, showValuesCheck.checked);\n      }\n\n      drawBtn.addEventListener('click', draw);\n      // initial draw\n      draw();\n    })();\n\n    // ===== Sierpinski triangle drawing =====\n    (function(){\n      const canvas = $('sierCanvas');\n      const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\n      const drawBtn = $('drawSier');\n      const depthInput = $('depth');\n\n      function clear(){\n        ctx.fillStyle = '#fff';\n        ctx.fillRect(0,0,canvas.width,canvas.height);\n      }\n\n      function drawTriangle(a, b, c){\n        ctx.beginPath();\n        ctx.moveTo(a.x, a.y);\n        ctx.lineTo(b.x, b.y);\n        ctx.lineTo(c.x, c.y);\n        ctx.closePath();\n        ctx.fill();\n      }\n\n      function midpoint(p, q){\n        return { x: (p.x+q.x)/2, y: (p.y+q.y)/2 };\n      }\n\n      function sierpinski(a, b, c, depth){\n        if (depth === 0){\n          drawTriangle(a,b,c);\n        } else {\n          const ab = midpoint(a,b);\n          const bc = midpoint(b,c);\n          const ca = midpoint(c,a);\n          sierpinski(a, ab, ca, depth-1);\n          sierpinski(ab, b, bc, depth-1);\n          sierpinski(ca, bc, c, depth-1);\n        }\n      }\n\n      function render(){\n        const depth = Math.max(0, Math.min(7, parseInt(depthInput.value) || 0));\n        clear();\n        // background triangle outline\n        const margin = 20;\n        const a = { x: canvas.width/2, y: margin };\n        const b = { x: margin, y: canvas.height - margin };\n        const c = { x: canvas.width - margin, y: canvas.height - margin };\n\n        // fill the whole large triangle white\n        ctx.fillStyle = '#fff';\n        ctx.fillRect(0,0,canvas.width,canvas.height);\n\n        // draw filled black triangles for Sierpinski (we fill the subtriangles)\n        ctx.fillStyle = '#111';\n        sierpinski(a,b,c,depth);\n\n        // outline\n        ctx.strokeStyle = '#444';\n        ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n        ctx.beginPath();\n        ctx.moveTo(a.x,a.y);\n        ctx.lineTo(b.x,b.y);\n        ctx.lineTo(c.x,c.y);\n        ctx.closePath();\n        ctx.stroke();\n      }\n\n      drawBtn.addEventListener('click', render);\n      // initial render\n      render();\n    })();\n\n    // Small accessibility: respond to Enter on inputs for quick runs\n    (function(){\n      const factN = $('factN');\n      factN.addEventListener('keyup', (e)=>{ if(e.key === 'Enter') $('runFact').click(); });\n\n      $('fibN').addEventListener('keyup', (e)=>{ if(e.key === 'Enter') $('drawFib').click(); });\n      $('depth').addEventListener('keyup', (e)=>{ if(e.key === 'Enter') $('drawSier').click(); });\n    })();\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
